<span class="mainheader">2010 Program</span>

<dl>
The Arabidopsis 2010 program is supported by the <a href="http://www.nsf.gov/">U.S. National Science Foundation (NSF)</a>.  The goal of the program is to provide funding to enable researchers to determine the function of all Arabidopsis
genes by the year 2010.  The first grants were awarded in 2001 with new proposals funded each year.
